explanation: The solution uses the mathematical property that the amount of water that can be measured is a multiple of the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the capacities of the two jugs. The GCD is calculated using the Euclidean algorithm. The target can be reached if it is a multiple of the GCD and does not exceed the sum of the capacities of the two jugs.

